HEADWORD: genuflexion
<hw>gen`u*flex"ion</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>g⟦eacute⟧nuflexion</ets>, fr.
LL. <ets>genuflexio</ets>, fr. L. <ets>genu</ets> knee +
<ets>flexio</ets> a bending, fr. <ets>flectere</ets>, <ets>flexum</ets>,
to bend. See <er>Knee</er>, <er>Flexible</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of
bending the knee, particularly in worship or reverence.</def>
<rj><au>Bp. Stillingfleet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
